      <title>Squirrel on Fire - Jeff&amp;#039;s ACWW Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/04/04/squirrel-on-fire/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/04/04/squirrel-on-fire/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sat, 05 Apr 2025 02:36:03 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-8047" class="post-8047 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Squirrel on Fire&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	 	 	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;Yesterday, I received my monthly bank statement in the mail. I earned 75,450 bells for the month.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Pascal was in town, and he told me that a sea bass is not an instrument.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/04/04/squirrel-on-fire/Array" alt="Pascal: A sea bass is not an instrument, maaannn." class="wp-image-8048" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;I think that depends on how you use it.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Robin told me that back in the day, spiders used to be as big as us! And you think you hate walking into a web &lt;em&gt;now&lt;/em&gt;, imagine back then! 🕸️&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/04/04/squirrel-on-fire/Array" alt="Robin: Back in the day, an average spider was the same size as us!" class="wp-image-8049" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Truffles has still been sick with a cold, so I gave her some more medicine yesterday and again today.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Tank told me that he was fishing in the river, and he caught a squid today! I find that hard to believe, since squid can only be caught in the ocean.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/04/04/squirrel-on-fire/Array" alt="Tank: I was fishing in the river and caught myself a squid!" class="wp-image-8050" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;Is Tank pulling a prank? Or did I just get hornswoggled?&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;A couple minutes later, I ran into Tank again as he was chatting with Caroline. Caroline told him that it was good to see him smiling.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/04/04/squirrel-on-fire/Array" alt="Caroline: Tank, it's so nice to see you smiling. you always look so happy, on my Wii." class="wp-image-8052" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;However, Tank denied being happy. He said he was just flexing his face muscles!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/04/04/squirrel-on-fire/Array" alt="Tank: I'm not happy! I'm flexing my face! I don't want my lips to start sagging!" class="wp-image-8051" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;After that, Caroline asked me for a new catchphrase to replace &amp;#8220;on my Wii.&amp;#8221; Her old phrase is a bit played out, after all. Since her coloring and hair look a bit like fire, I told her to say &amp;#8220;on fire.&amp;#8221; She liked the sound of it. 🔥&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/04/04/squirrel-on-fire/Array" alt="Caroline: Yes! On fire! I like the sound of that! It's me, on fire! It's fresh!" class="wp-image-8053" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;When I spoke with her again, she asked me to deliver a letter to Curt. I agreed to help out, and Curt told me that the letter warmed his cold, crabby heart. 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/04/04/squirrel-on-fire/Array" alt="Curt: Hm... That really warms my cold, crabby heart." class="wp-image-8054" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Caroline rewarded me with a green wall.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I recently posted a new Wild World video episode, featuring highlights from mid-February through late March. Here it is, if you haven&amp;#8217;t seen it yet:&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio"&gt;&lt;div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper"&gt; &lt;iframe loading="lazy" title="Animal Crossing: Wild World #75" width="840" height="473" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/QgsJlRp1fmk?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Just one last note: The flower fest is next week! Get ready to steal your neighbors&amp;#8217; flowers, if you play that way! 😆&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;img alt='' src='https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/04/04/squirrel-on-fire/Array' class='avatar avatar-49 photo' height='49' width='49'/&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/04/04/squirrel-on-fire/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-04-04T22:36:03-04:00"&gt;April 4, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-04-04T22:41:24-04:00"&gt;April 4, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt; &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/pascal-sea-bass.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>My Switch 2 Direct Thoughts - Jeff&amp;#039;s Gaming Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/blog/2025/04/02/my-switch-2-direct-thoughts/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/blog/2025/04/02/my-switch-2-direct-thoughts/</guid>
      <pubDate>Thu, 03 Apr 2025 00:54:16 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-5536" class="post-5536 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;My Switch 2 Direct Thoughts&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	 	 	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;Nintendo Switch 2 was fully revealed today in a Nintendo Direct&amp;#8230;including its release date of June 5th! 😮 I&amp;#8217;m going to talk about many parts of the Direct that interested me (for better or worse), and at the end I&amp;#8217;ll list my Top 3 most-wanted games and my Top 3 biggest disappointments. I won&amp;#8217;t be covering every announcement though, so watch the &lt;a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VrTVeYm4iIM" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener"&gt;full Direct&lt;/a&gt; yourself if you don&amp;#8217;t want to miss anything.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;h2 class="wp-block-heading"&gt;Mario Kart World&lt;/h2&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The first reveal was the Mario Kart game that was previously teased. It&amp;#8217;s called Mario Kart World, and it looks beautiful.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/blog/2025/04/02/my-switch-2-direct-thoughts/Array" alt="Mario Kart World screenshot." class="wp-image-5544" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;It even has a cow riding a scooter. 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/blog/2025/04/02/my-switch-2-direct-thoughts/Array" alt="A cow racing in Mario Kart World." class="wp-image-5545" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;One interesting thing is that you can venture off the race tracks and drive just about everywhere. In the Grand Prix mode, you&amp;#8217;ll not only race on four tracks in each cup, but you&amp;#8217;ll drive &lt;em&gt;to &lt;/em&gt;each course as part of the competition. I&amp;#8217;m not sure exactly how that factors into the scoring, but I guess we&amp;#8217;ll see. There are also 24 drivers in each race, a new record for the series.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio"&gt;&lt;div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper"&gt; &lt;iframe title="Mario Kart World – Nintendo Direct | Nintendo Switch 2" width="840" height="473" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/3pE23YTYEZM?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;    &lt;p&gt;A &amp;#8220;Free Roam&amp;#8221; mode also lets you explore the whole world (with friends, if you wish) and take photos at certain locations. This sounds like a lot of fun. The ability to explore the lands between courses reminds me of my &lt;a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mRUDe49Gdpk" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener"&gt;Animal Crossing idea&lt;/a&gt; of being able to explore the lands between Animal Crossing towns.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;One trivial annoyance is that the game has the same abbreviation (MKW) as a previous game in the series, Mario Kart Wii. I wish they had just called it Mario Kart 9. I don&amp;#8217;t know why they even started a numbering system seven games into the series if they were only going to stick with it for two games. 😛&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;h2 class="wp-block-heading"&gt;GameChat&lt;/h2&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Nintendo unveiled GameChat, a new voice chat feature that uses the system&amp;#8217;s built-in microphone. You can also share your screen with friends as you chat together&amp;#8230;even if you&amp;#8217;re playing different games!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/blog/2025/04/02/my-switch-2-direct-thoughts/Array" alt="Gamers playing different games while chatting." class="wp-image-5546" sizes="auto, (max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;The new C button brings up the chat menu. There&amp;#8217;s also a Switch 2 Camera that&amp;#8217;s sold separately that allows video chat. You can even let everyone see live video of yourself as you play. I&amp;#8217;m not sure who asked for this, but the ability is there. 🤷&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/blog/2025/04/02/my-switch-2-direct-thoughts/Array" alt="Four players playing Super Mario World while video chatting." class="wp-image-5547" sizes="auto, (max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;As a (very) introverted person, I&amp;#8217;m not interested in any of this stuff. But having a separate accessory reminded me a bit of Wii Speak.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="482" src="https://www.jvgs.net/blog/2025/04/02/my-switch-2-direct-thoughts/Array" alt="Wii Speak vs. We Peek (The Switch 2 Camera)" class="wp-image-5539" sizes="auto, (max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;The GameChat features will normally require a Nintendo Switch Online membership. But it will be available to try for free through March 31, 2026.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;h2 class="wp-block-heading"&gt;Upgrades of Switch Games&lt;/h2&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Many Switch games will have upgraded versions that offer improved graphics, GameChat features, stronger rumble, and/or new control methods (each JoyCon 2 can be used as a mouse in certain games). You can even get a virtual GPS for Link in Tears of the Kingdom to guide you towards shrines and Koroks you haven&amp;#8217;t found yet. 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/blog/2025/04/02/my-switch-2-direct-thoughts/Array" alt="Voice navigation app for The Legend of Zelda: Tears of the Kingdom." class="wp-image-5548" sizes="auto, (max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Upgrade packs generally must be purchased. But Nintendo Switch Online + Expansion Pack members can upgrade the Zelda Breath of the Wild and Tears of the Kingdom games for free. (I only have the regular Switch Online account, so that certainly leaves me out.)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;h2 class="wp-block-heading"&gt;Nintendo GameCube Classics&lt;/h2&gt;    &lt;p&gt;On Switch 2, Expansion Pack subscribers will have access to a selection of Nintendo GameCube games. It includes The Legend of Zelda: Wind Waker, SoulCalibur II, and F-Zero GX. Multiplayer games will also have online play. Additional games will be added, but there&amp;#8217;s no sign of Animal Crossing so far.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/blog/2025/04/02/my-switch-2-direct-thoughts/Array" alt="Nintendo GameCube: Nintendo Classics" class="wp-image-5549" sizes="auto, (max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;h2 class="wp-block-heading"&gt;EA Sports Returns&lt;/h2&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I was happy to see that EA Sports is returning to Nintendo for the first time since the Wii days! I haven&amp;#8217;t bought many sports games in recent years, but I&amp;#8217;ll probably buy a new Madden game for the first time since Madden NFL 12. 😆&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;h2 class="wp-block-heading"&gt;Donkey Kong Bananza&lt;/h2&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Perhaps my biggest surprise of the Direct was Donkey Kong Bananza. It&amp;#8217;s a 3D Donkey Kong game, coming out July 17th. I definitely didn&amp;#8217;t see this one coming!&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio"&gt;&lt;div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper"&gt; &lt;iframe loading="lazy" title="Donkey Kong Bananza – Nintendo Direct | Nintendo Switch 2" width="840" height="473" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/mIddsPkdX9U?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Donkey Kong 64 is one of my favorite 3D platformers of all time, and I&amp;#8217;ve been waiting a long time for another 3D Donkey Kong game. But from the trailer, it seems to be more fast-paced and action-heavy than the somewhat easygoing exploration of DK64. But we&amp;#8217;ll see how it turns out!&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I will say that I&amp;#8217;m not a fan of the art style of DK himself. The facial expressions are over-the-top cartoony that border on cringey.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="275" src="https://www.jvgs.net/blog/2025/04/02/my-switch-2-direct-thoughts/Array" alt="The faces of Donkey Kong in DK Bananza." class="wp-image-5541" sizes="auto, (max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;h2 class="wp-block-heading"&gt;The Price&lt;/h2&gt;    &lt;p&gt;One of the biggest disappointments came after the Direct was over, when the pricing was revealed. The Switch 2 by itself will cost $450 (USD), and the Mario Kart World bundle will cost $500. Nintendo has previously tried to keep their system costs from being super high in the past, but this seems excessive. That&amp;#8217;s a whopping 50% higher than the original Switch&amp;#8217;s $300 initial price tag!&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;While it&amp;#8217;s true that there are other consoles (such as PS5) in the same ~$450 price range, Switch 2 is not on par with those. Nintendo&amp;#8217;s systems (at least in the past 20 years) have been significantly less powerful than their competitors, lagging behind by a generation or two. By all accounts, Switch 2 seems to be about as powerful as a PlayStation 4&amp;#8230;a 12-year-old system. I just don&amp;#8217;t think we should be paying PS5 money for PS4-level tech.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;But perhaps even worse is the price of games: It&amp;#8217;s been reported that many Switch 2 games will cost $80 for digital versions, and up to $90 for physical versions! At those prices, I&amp;#8217;ll be much less likely to take chances on games I&amp;#8217;m not certain about.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;For a company that has traditionally tried to provide a good value for consumers, this seems uncharacteristically greedy of Nintendo. This sentiment has certainly soured the mood of this reveal.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;h2 class="wp-block-heading"&gt;My Most Wanted&lt;/h2&gt;    &lt;p&gt;After today&amp;#8217;s announcements and trailers, here are my top 3 most-wanted Switch 2 games.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;ol class="wp-block-list"&gt; &lt;li&gt;Metroid Prime 4. Even though not a lot was shown of it today, it remains the Switch 2 game I want most. But unfortunately, it still doesn&amp;#8217;t have a specific release date.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;Mario Kart World. It looks really good, and the large worlds and exploration should provide a lot of replay value.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;Donkey Kong Bananza. Even if it&amp;#8217;s not another Donkey Kong 64, it should be a lot of fun. And who knows, maybe it will recapture some of the monkey magic I&amp;#8217;m looking for.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ol&gt;    &lt;h2 class="wp-block-heading"&gt;Biggest Disappointments&lt;/h2&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The Direct, and subsequent news, certainly provided some disappointments that kept this reveal from being great. Here are my three biggest disappointments.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;ol class="wp-block-list"&gt; &lt;li&gt;No Animal Crossing. As most of you know, I&amp;#8217;m a huge Animal Crossing fan. And I was hoping for something AC related, at least. Nothing was announced, not even a tease of the GameCube game coming to Expansion Pack. &lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;The price. The cost of hardware and software feels like a punch to the gut. It actually makes me glad that Tomodachi Life: Living the Dream and Rhythm Heaven Groove are going to be for the original Switch, not Switch 2. 😛&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;The lack of first-party games, especially at launch. Mario Kart World is the only real first-party game at launch, and it feels weird to not have a proper Mario or Zelda game at launch. I prefer having a single-player action or adventure game with a new system. As good as Mario Kart may be, it&amp;#8217;s not the same.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ol&gt;    &lt;p&gt;How about you all? Are you happy with the Direct? Disappointed? Let me know in the comments!&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;img alt='' src='https://www.jvgs.net/blog/2025/04/02/my-switch-2-direct-thoughts/Array' class='avatar avatar-49 photo' height='49' width='49'/&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/blog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/blog/2025/04/02/my-switch-2-direct-thoughts/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-04-02T20:54:16-04:00"&gt;April 2, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-04-04T14:45:44-04:00"&gt;April 4, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt; &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/blog/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/mk9-sm.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Pete Drops In - Jeff&amp;#039;s Animal Crossing Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/03/30/pete-drops-in/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/03/30/pete-drops-in/</guid>
      <pubDate>Mon, 31 Mar 2025 02:30:35 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-5919" class="post-5919 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Pete Drops In&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;Today, I found some airmail from Bangle the tiger. She has moved out of town, unfortunately.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/03/30/pete-drops-in/Array" alt="To Jeff, I'm leaving town, and I'm not telling anyone where I'm going, but don't you worry! I'm off on a grand adventure that's totally going to rule! Wish me luck in my new life. Don't forget me! -Bangle!" class="wp-image-5922" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I just happened to be playing around 5:00 p.m., so Pete dropped in right after I finished reading my mail. He said that I can&amp;#8217;t just give mail directly to him, I have to take it to the post office.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/03/30/pete-drops-in/Array" alt="Pete: If you want to mail a letter, you can't just give it to me. Take it to the Post Office." class="wp-image-5923" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;And he even told me what Phyllis makes him do in the middle of the night!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/03/30/pete-drops-in/Array" alt="Pete: Sometimes, Phyllis even needs me to deliver mail in the middle of the night! That's the worst!" class="wp-image-5924" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;At the lake, I ran into Baabara. She said that every time it rains, the weather gets warmer. I don&amp;#8217;t think that&amp;#8217;s true at all; I think she&amp;#8217;s just trying to pull the wool over my eyes. 😛&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/03/30/pete-drops-in/Array" alt="Baabara: They say every time it rains, the weather gets a little warmer, and I guess it's true, daahling." class="wp-image-5926" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Actually, there seems to be a series of &lt;s&gt;lies&lt;/s&gt; dialogue about the cherry blossoms that start appearing in early April. &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/03/30/pete-drops-in/Array" alt="Static: Now that I think about it, most of the trees in town are starting to put out little flower buds." class="wp-image-5927" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Several of my villagers were talking about the upcoming cherry blossoms. Puck wanted to have a picnic beneath them, and that sounds like such a cute idea.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/03/30/pete-drops-in/Array" alt="Puck: Have you ever had a picnic beneath the cherry blossoms? I'm already looking forward to it, brrrrrrrrr..." class="wp-image-5928" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I ran into Bangle&amp;#8217;s replacement, Lulu the hippo. She previously lived in Forest back in 2011, and she also currently lives in my other town, Ohio. I&amp;#8217;m not a big fan of her, but &lt;em&gt;this &lt;/em&gt;Lulu actually did seem pretty nice so far. She gave me a free cherry!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/03/30/pete-drops-in/Array" alt="Lulu: I totally picked this one cherry tree clean, but I can't eat that much fruit myself, yaaaawl." class="wp-image-5929" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;I think you could.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Over at the wishing well, Belle was heartbroken to learn that I caught a coelacanth before she did.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/03/30/pete-drops-in/Array" alt="Belle: Sigh. I was trying so hard, too..." class="wp-image-5930" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;At the police station, I tried on a few shirts that were in the lost and found. I ultimately decided to keep the light line shirt on, even though it wasn&amp;#8217;t anything special. I was just tired of wearing the stars, I guess. 😛&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Kody asked me if I&amp;#8217;d like to manage his new swimming team. I usually answer &amp;#8220;yes&amp;#8221; to these, but I wanted to see how he&amp;#8217;d respond if I declined. &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/03/30/pete-drops-in/Array" alt="Kody: Hmm, I guess swimming isn't  very popular... Watching it is such a blast..." class="wp-image-5932" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;There&amp;#8217;s a slight mistake there, with two spaces in between &amp;#8220;isn&amp;#8217;t&amp;#8221; and &amp;#8220;very.&amp;#8221; 😛&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I later ran into Baabara again, and she said she&amp;#8217;s going to stay up late tonight. &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/03/30/pete-drops-in/Array" alt="Baabara: I'm going to stay up late tonight, because I feel good. And because I stay up as late as I wish." class="wp-image-5933" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I can&amp;#8217;t argue with her logic this time!&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;My latest video shows eight things I&amp;#8217;d like to see in the next Animal Crossing game. And one event from the GameCube game made my list. Please check out the video if you haven&amp;#8217;t seen it yet:&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio"&gt;&lt;div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper"&gt; &lt;iframe loading="lazy" title="8 Things I&amp;#039;d Like to See in Animal Crossing 6" width="660" height="371" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/mRUDe49Gdpk?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I&amp;#8217;ll be back with more in April! Hope to see you then!&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/03/30/pete-drops-in/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-03-30T22:30:35-04:00"&gt;March 30, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-03-30T22:31:58-04:00"&gt;March 30, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/ac-bangle-out-sm.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Four Turtles - Jeff&amp;#039;s New Horizons Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/03/29/four-turtles/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/03/29/four-turtles/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 30 Mar 2025 01:57:35 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-8681" class="post-8681 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Four Turtles&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;On Monday, I went out to Lottie&amp;#8217;s Island and took some close-up photos of a blue bird that was sitting on the island map. So cute! You can also spot Julian the unicorn reading in the background.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/03/29/four-turtles/Array" alt="A blue bird is perched on the map on Lottie's Island, while Julian is reading in the background." class="wp-image-8683" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Wednesday (March 26th) was Louie&amp;#8217;s birthday. So I bought a gift for him, wrapped it up in jungle green wrapping paper, and headed over to his party.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/03/29/four-turtles/Array" alt="Louie, at his birthday party: Alright! I wonder what it is!" class="wp-image-8684" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I gave him a Japanese dresser that I bought at Nook&amp;#8217;s Cranny for 8,400 bells. Louie noticed that it was an expensive gift, and he seemed very grateful. By the way, Ankha was also at his party; you can see a sliver of her face in the above screenshot. 😆&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Hippeux the hideous hippo was hanging out at the campsite for the third time.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/03/29/four-turtles/Array" alt="Hippeux, at the campsite: Although...I'm not much of a spring hippo myself." class="wp-image-8685" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;So go on and bounce on out of here.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Yesterday, I went out to see Katrina on Harv&amp;#8217;s Island. I paid her to tell my fortune, and she told me that my luck with money will diminish. So I paid her 10,000 bells for purification.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Today, I received my letter from Katrina. She sent me another gold turtle figurine! That&amp;#8217;s four of them in four tries! She&amp;#8217;s supposed to have four different items, and from what I&amp;#8217;ve heard, they&amp;#8217;re supposed to be random! How un-&lt;em&gt;four&lt;/em&gt;-tunate. It&amp;#8217;s &lt;em&gt;turtle-y&lt;/em&gt; unfair!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/03/29/four-turtles/Array" alt="Jeff, surrounded by four gold turtle figurines." class="wp-image-8686" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;They&amp;#8217;re not even ninja turtles.&lt;br&gt;TMNT = Too Many Needless Turtles&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I encountered Pascal while diving, and he wondered if the oceans are salty because they&amp;#8217;re made of the Earth&amp;#8217;s tears. &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/03/29/four-turtles/Array" alt="Pascal: The ocean is salty, just like tears. Ever wonder if the earth is just crying it out?" class="wp-image-8687" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I wrapped up my night with a concert at the plaza. K.K. playeded a particularly plodding performance of &amp;#8220;Pondering.&amp;#8221; Bob was the only villager with me for the show, although Louie did walk through near the end of the song. 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="550" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/03/29/four-turtles/Array" alt="Louie walks through a concert (while holding a purse) as Jeff and Bob were trying to enjoy K.K. Slider's show." class="wp-image-8682" sizes="auto, (max-width: 550px) 100vw, 550px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Here are a few other quick notes about the past week or so:&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;ul class="wp-block-list"&gt; &lt;li&gt;Merengue sent me another copy of her photo last week, to thank me for her birthday gift.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;Last Friday, I sold 22 fish to C.J. for 255,750 bells.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;On Monday, I sold 15 bugs to Flick for 73,500 bells.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;Today, I returned a lost item to Ankha. She rewarded me with a cardigan school uniform top.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I recently posted a new video taking a look at eight things I&amp;#8217;d like to see in the next Animal Crossing game. Please give it a watch if you haven&amp;#8217;t seen it yet!&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio"&gt;&lt;div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper"&gt; &lt;iframe loading="lazy" title="8 Things I&amp;#039;d Like to See in Animal Crossing 6" width="660" height="371" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/mRUDe49Gdpk?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I&amp;#8217;ll see you next time!&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/03/29/four-turtles/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-03-29T21:57:35-04:00"&gt;March 29, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-03-29T21:57:36-04:00"&gt;March 29, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/bluebird-sm.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>The Lolly-Pop Gift - Jeff&amp;#039;s New Leaf Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/03/28/lolly-pop-gift/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/03/28/lolly-pop-gift/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sat, 29 Mar 2025 03:09:44 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-18165" class="post-18165 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;The Lolly-Pop Gift&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;Yesterday was Lolly&amp;#8217;s birthday, and I made sure to attend her birthday party. I gave her a candy jar, so that she could eat some &lt;em&gt;lolly&lt;/em&gt;-pops. 🍭&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/03/28/lolly-pop-gift/Array" alt="Lolly: Ooh, a candy jar. How thoughtful of you. Thanks!" class="wp-image-18166" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Rolf was also at her party, but he only seemed to be thinking of himself. Come on, Rolf, it&amp;#8217;s Lolly&amp;#8217;s day!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/03/28/lolly-pop-gift/Array" alt="Rolf: I'm starting to worry whether I'll get anyone at MY inevitable party. You think anyone will show up?" class="wp-image-18167" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;You&amp;#8217;ll have one friend at your party, just like everyone else.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;There was a tent at the campsite, and I found Derwin the duck inside. He&amp;#8217;s kinda cute&amp;#8230;in an unconventional way.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/03/28/lolly-pop-gift/Array" alt="Derwin: I pretty much just decided to camp here on a whim, but it ended up being an awesome decision!" class="wp-image-18168" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Today, Lolly sent me a letter thanking me for the birthday gift. She sent me something, too: a trash bin! Hmm, is this a sign that she didn&amp;#8217;t like the candy? 😛&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Mira asked me for some new furniture, and she said anything would be fine. So I gave her a sloppy sink that I had in my pockets. (I already have another one in storage.)&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/03/28/lolly-pop-gift/Array" alt="Mira: Oh! A sloppy sink? Good call!" class="wp-image-18169" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;In return, she gave me a robo-stereo. 🤖&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;There was another camper today, and this time it was Monique. She was one of my mortal enemies from the early days of my GameCube town. Yuck, no thanks.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/03/28/lolly-pop-gift/Array" alt="Monique, at the campsite: I wouldn't call it a midlife crisis. But I feel like I need to make a change." class="wp-image-18170" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I found a lost item (a bag) on the ground today, and I never would have guessed what was inside: It contained petunia protein shakes that belonged to Boots!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/03/28/lolly-pop-gift/Array" alt="Boots: My new petunia protein shakes are gonna beef me up like never before!" class="wp-image-18171" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;He gave me a nice bug zapper as my reward.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Cube told me that he dreamed about me eating sauerkraut until I swelled up like a balloon! That&amp;#8217;s pretty much what happens with all the gas that sauerkraut gives you! 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/03/28/lolly-pop-gift/Array" alt="Cube: In my dream last night, you were eating sauerkraut until your belly swelled up like a balloon!" class="wp-image-18172" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;He was worried, but also a bit jealous. 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/03/28/lolly-pop-gift/Array" alt="Cube: I was all worried for you. But I was also kind of jealous, on Toy Day." class="wp-image-18173" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;He also asked me to catch a pill bug for him. It didn&amp;#8217;t take me long to track one down, and Cube gave me a natty tee in return.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Before wrapping up my game for the day, I put my money into my savings account. My balance has reached 133 million bells.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/03/28/lolly-pop-gift/Array" alt="Your current balance is 133,000,000 bells." class="wp-image-18174" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Yesterday, I posted a video of eight things I&amp;#8217;d like to see in the next Animal Crossing game. Of course, multiplayer games (like the tours in New Leaf) made my list. I hope you&amp;#8217;ll check out the full list:&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio"&gt;&lt;div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper"&gt; &lt;iframe loading="lazy" title="8 Things I&amp;#039;d Like to See in Animal Crossing 6" width="660" height="371" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/mRUDe49Gdpk?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/03/28/lolly-pop-gift/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-03-28T23:09:44-04:00"&gt;March 28, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-03-28T23:29:29-04:00"&gt;March 28, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/20250327_HNI_0045.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
