      <title>Snuggle Bunnies - Jeff&amp;#039;s ACWW Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/03/28/snuggle-bunnies/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/03/28/snuggle-bunnies/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sat, 29 Mar 2025 01:15:24 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-8030" class="post-8030 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Snuggle Bunnies&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	 	 	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;On Wednesday, I ran a long way (from all the way down on the beach, up to the north wall) to shoot down a balloon present. I found a wave breaker inside. It would&amp;#8217;ve been more useful on the beach. 😉 🌊&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Robin wanted to sell me a royal shirt, and she asked how much I would spend. I put the slider close to the minimum (1 bell), and she called me a wuss. And then she still made me pay 480 bells for the shirt. &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/03/28/snuggle-bunnies/Array" alt="Robin: Wow, you're still such a big wuss, huh." class="wp-image-8031" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;Excuse me for not wanting to spend all my money on a shirt I don&amp;#8217;t want.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Yesterday, Caroline told me she&amp;#8217;ll sometimes pretend to cry, just to make her friend upset. I had the option to say &amp;#8220;That&amp;#8217;s funny!&amp;#8221; or &amp;#8220;That&amp;#8217;s terrible,&amp;#8221; and I chose the former (just to see how she&amp;#8217;d react). She was really happy about my response, and she said we should be best friends now. 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/03/28/snuggle-bunnies/Array" alt="Caroline: From now on, let's you and me be best friends! This'll be so fun, on my Wii!" class="wp-image-8032" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I ran into her again a few minutes later, and she showed me a random letter she received. It was signed from &amp;#8220;a certain furry someone.&amp;#8221; 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/03/28/snuggle-bunnies/Array" alt="To Caroline, I'm not fat! I'm just fluffy! -A certain furry someone" class="wp-image-8033" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Today, I listened in on a conversation between Robin and Whitney behind town hall. Whitney said she makes a cute face when she eats, and Robin said that she likes to stuff her face with marshmallows.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/03/28/snuggle-bunnies/Array" alt="Robin: I like to stuff my face with as many marshmallows as I can." class="wp-image-8034" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;She then tries to say &amp;#8220;Snuggle Bunnies&amp;#8221; with her mouth full. This is pretty much exactly the &amp;#8220;chubby bunny&amp;#8221; challenge.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/03/28/snuggle-bunnies/Array" alt="Robin: Then, I try to say snuggle bunnies! You should try it! It's the funnest thing ever!" class="wp-image-8035" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Whitney said that she loves to play Snuggle Bunnies too, and she suggested that they should get together and play it sometime.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/03/28/snuggle-bunnies/Array" alt="Whitney: We should totally get together sometime and play Snuggle Bunnies." class="wp-image-8036" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Whitney concluded that their personalities are so similar that them hanging out together is like looking in a mirror.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Truffles was sick with a cold (or was it the swine flu?), so I gave her some medicine. Get well soon, Truffles.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;img alt='' src='https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/03/28/snuggle-bunnies/Array' class='avatar avatar-49 photo' height='49' width='49'/&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/03/28/snuggle-bunnies/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-03-28T21:15:24-04:00"&gt;March 28, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-03-28T21:33:39-04:00"&gt;March 28, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt; &lt;/article&gt;</description>
